As a proud citizen of USA, a nation built on the deeply spiritual principles of Life, Liberty and the Pursuit of Happiness, I absolutely love CLAW, their long term vision and their different programs - Lifeskills and Mindset Training courses like GRIT, their treks, river rafting expeditions, bike expeditions, Skill and Endurance challenge competitions like Soul of Steel and so many others. This organization has a HUGE heart and seems to be adept at doing great things very quietly. For example, if someone shows highest merit/talent for any of their programs like Soul of Steel (SOS) but doesn’t have the funds to pay the fees, CLAW takes genuine interest in meritorious candidates and does everything they can to fund such people out of their own profits. They don’t seem to clamor for publicity in the name of charity or DE&I and they seem to have great interest in going about their good deeds in a very dignified way. 
What I love most about CLAW is - They are very simple people. They excel in actions. The content, planning, execution for each of their programs is top notch. But if you talk to them, they’ll make you feel like you are the smart one. Ha ha 🙂🙂
Ms. Gul Panag has earned my lifelong respect by participating with CLAW. 
USA sends CLAW its very best wishes

firstComment:
Dear Sanjay Agarwal,
I am writing to express my deep disappointment and frustration with the level of service I have received during my home loan application process with your bank.
PFA Screenshots with this email for your reference.
On 28th July 2023, your executive accompanied me to finalize the deal for the Flat num A-905 at 38 Divine project in Kondhwa. Based on their communication, I went ahead and booked the Flat, providing a cheque of 8 Lakhs as an initial payment. The total cost of the Flat is 65 Lakhs 50 Thousand, out of which I am paying 25 Lakhs 50 Thousand, and the bank is supposed to finance the remaining 40 Lakhs. Possession Date is December 2025. Payment will be made in tranches.
I was promised to receive the entire status of the project, technical findings and the approval letter by today afternoon. However, despite my efforts to contact your representatives since morning, I have not received any response or updates. The lack of communication, efficiency, and professionalism has been extremely disappointing. After multiple calls no audacity to call back.
Due to the slow, inefficient, and unpleasant service provided by your employees, I have no choice but to cancel my home loan application with AU Small Finance Bank. I kindly request you to process the cancellation and initiate the refund of the money I paid, which includes 5900rs and 500rs fees for credit check.
Throughout this process, I have encountered numerous challenges and frustrations. The lack of transparency and the inability to provide timely updates on my application status have made this experience utterly unpleasant.
I believe in providing feedback to improve services, and I hope my unfortunate experience will be taken constructively. I have decided to opt for a home loan from another bank, Kotak Mahindra, which has been my preferred choice from the beginning but my car loan is unfortunately from your bank so thought I will get premium service from your bank hence came knocking your door for home loan but it turned out to be a nightmare.
I sincerely hope that you take this matter seriously and take necessary steps to rectify the issues within your organization. I trus
